column1: 1,B,B,B,B,+4,HIGHER,"MAXIMUM BUYER CONVICTION - All four factors aligned perfectly. Rotation shows buyers in control, range extended up confirming initiative buying, bottom tail proves sellers tested lower but failed (rejection), and composite opened low and moved up showing strong buyer response. This is textbook buyer dominance.  Next day should attempt to auction higher with high confidence.  Look for continuation or short covering rally."

2,B,B,B,N,+3,HIGHER,"STRONG BUYER DAY - Three critical factors show buyer control.  Positive rotation indicates buyers winning time-price opportunities, upward extension shows initiative buyers expanding value, bottom tail confirms lower prices were rejected.  Neutral composite (opened mid-range) doesn't contradict the buyer narrative. High confidence for higher auction attempt. Market showing clear directional conviction despite mid-range open."

3,B,B,B,S,+2,HIGHER,"BUYER DOMINANT WITH CAVEAT - Strong buyer signals in rotation, extension, and tail, but composite shows opened high and moved down (seller characteristic). This suggests early weakness that was overcome by aggressive buyers. The fact that buyers still extended range up AND left bottom tail despite poor composite structure shows strong underlying demand. Buyer conviction outweighs the composite conflict. Moderate-high confidence for higher attempt."

4,B,B,B,X,+3,HIGHER,"STRONG BUYER CONVICTION - Three solid buyer factors with N/A composite (extremely wide range day makes composite analysis impossible). Positive rotation shows time favored buyers, upward extension confirms initiative, bottom tail shows seller failure.  The absence of composite data doesn't weaken the case - three aligned factors provide high confidence. Expect higher auction attempt, possibly trending day continuation."

5,B,B,N,B,+3,HIGHER,"STRONG BUYER CONTROL - Rotation positive, extension up, composite bullish (opened low, moved up). The neutral tail (both ends or neither) doesn't negate three strong buyer signals. This pattern suggests market is in discovery mode moving higher - both tails indicate two-sided acceptance at new levels or a balanced profile while trending.  High confidence for continuation higher."

6,B,B,N,N,+2,HIGHER,"BUYER IN CONTROL, MODERATE STRENGTH - Rotation and extension both favor buyers, showing time and initiative on buyer side. Neutral tail and neutral composite suggest mid-range activity without extreme testing. This is a steady buyer day without dramatic rejection - think gradual accumulation. Moderate confidence for higher attempt, though less explosive than when all factors align.  Watch for continuation vs. consolidation."

7,B,B,N,S,+1,NEUTRAL,"MIXED SIGNALS - SLIGHT BUYER EDGE - Buyer rotation and extension conflict with seller composite (opened high, moved down). Neutral tail adds no clarity. This suggests market opened with seller advantage, but buyers took control during the session to extend range up. The battle is real here.  While buyers won the day, the poor composite structure and lack of clear tail rejection make next-day direction uncertain. Expect balancing or cautious continuation."

8,B,B,N,X,+2,HIGHER,"BUYER SHOWING STRENGTH - Positive rotation and upward extension both confirm buyer initiative.  Neutral tail suggests no extreme testing/rejection. Market likely in trending mode with wide range preventing composite analysis."

9,B,B,S,B,+2,HIGHER,"BUYER PREVAILS DESPITE TOP TAIL - Interesting dynamic:  buyers controlled rotation and extended range up, composite shows classic buyer structure (low open, moved up), BUT there's a top tail indicating higher prices were rejected. This suggests buyers pushed aggressively but met resistance at highs. However, the overall structure still favors buyers 3-1.  Moderate confidence for higher, but watch for resistance.  Buyers in control but hitting ceiling."

Mixed message:  initiative was buyer-driven, but outcome shows resistance. Expect balancing day or choppy action as market digests the failed breakout attempt."

But top tail shows rejection at highs, and seller composite (opened high, moved down) indicates underlying weakness. This is a bull trap pattern - looks bullish but has bearish undertones. Low confidence either direction.  Expect balancing day as market sorts out the conflict."
